      <div id="slide" class="slide1">      
        <div class="inside-slide">
          <div class="slide-title">
            <p>What is a solar flare</p>
          </div>
          <div class="slide-content content1">
            <ul>
              <li>A solar flare is a large explosion in the Sun's atmosphere that can release an amazing amount of energy.</li>
              <li>The approximate energy release is 6 x 10<sup>25</sup> joules of energy.</li>
              <li>That is equivalent to millions of 100-megaton hydrogen bombs exploding at the same time or ten million times greater than
              the energy released by a volcanic erupition.</li> 
              <li>These energy bursts can be about 1/6 of the total output of the sun's energy each second.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="span-8">
            <%= link_to image_tag("flare2-thumb.jpg", :id => "below-gallery", :class=>"media-in-slide"),
              '/images/flare2.jpg', :rel => "prettyPhoto[earthquake_screens_helper]", :title => "Solar flares with the sun blocked out for better visualization."%>
              <%= image_tag("flare2.jpg", :class => "earthquake_screen") %>
            </div>
            <div class="span-10">
              <p>
              Click the image to enlarge. The image has the sun's solar disk blocked out so the solar flare can be visualized better.
              </p>
            </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slide-number-left">
              <p>1</p>
            </div>
            <div class="slide-number-right">
              <p>1</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
